[diag-shell@&lt;sensor&gt; ~]$ corelight-client configuration update --bro.exporters.mcdz49j44z.debug_mode true

corelight-client error: argument {help}: invalid choice: 'true' (choose from 'help')

From provided logs;
 17:50:26.296390 - Client Hello (OUT) 
17:50:26.299488 - Server Hello (IN) &lt;&lt; (3ms later - server responded!)
17:50:26.299602 - Change Cipher (OUT) 
17:50:26.299851 - Client Hello #2 (OUT) (TLS 1.3 Hello Retry)
17:50:27.301012 - Waiting…  &lt;&lt; (1 second poll loop starts)
… forever polling, server never responds to 2nd Client Hello &nbsp;
The server IS responding initially (Server Hello in 3ms), then goes completely silent after the TLS 1.3 Hello Retry.
&nbsp;
Quick Test to force TLS 1.2 didn't work. Likely, their broker is accepting only TLS 1.3
 curl -vvk --tlsv1.2 --tls-max 1.2 https://fleet_ip:1443/ &nbsp;

